title: Married At First Sight's Jessika Power goes bungy jumping in Cairns
text:
She's been enjoying a relaxing holiday in Cairns, Queensland this week.

But Jessika Power turned things up a notch on Wednesday, when she swapped her hotel swimming pool for a thrilling outdoor adventure.

The Married At First Sight star celebrated her 28th birthday by going bungy jumping.

Taking the plunge! Married At First Sight's Jessika Power went bungy jumping in Cairns on Wednesday to celebrate her 28th birthday

She took the plunge off the top of Australia's only bungy jumping tower, which is operated by AJ Hackett Cairns.

Jessika, who wore blue and red shorts and a matching T-shirt, looked nervous and excited before her big leap.

She smiled with anticipation while being fitted with harnesses and listened carefully to a safety briefing from her instructor.

Adrenaline junkie: Jessika leaped off the top of Australia's only bungy jumping tower, which is operated by AJ Hackett Cairns

After her exhilarating jump, Jessika shared a video to Instagram in which she breathlessly spoke of her adrenaline rush.

'So I just did my first fall, woo!' she said.

'Did my first fall, I got one more off the roof... I'm dying to ride the BMX, can't wait!' she added while regaining her composure.

'I just did my first fall!' After her exhilarating jump, Jessika shared a video to Instagram in which she breathlessly spoke of her adrenaline rush

On Wednesday, Jessika shared several throwback photos to Instagram of herself as a child to commemorate her 28th birthday.

The pictures showed just how much she has changed physically over the years, but her cheeky smile has remained the same.

Jessika, a former administrative assistant from Perth, rose to fame on Married At First Sight earlier this year.
